items.synopsis: England make a strong start with the bat after Steve Smith's 32nd Test hundred led Australia 416 all out on the second morning of the second Ashes Test at Lord's. Follow all the action in our live blog.

title.children: Lyon breaks through after England's openers put Australia on the back foot

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Well. Well. That was one hell of a session for England going at better than five runs an over and making this bowling attack look harmless. Mitchell Starc is looking particularly brutal on his recall, going at 7.8 an over in his seven. The pitch isn't doing anything, so we'll see if Australia can muster something in the final session after a cuppa.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: TEA: England 1-145 (Duckett 62, Pope 32)

props.alt: Ben Duckett and Alex Carey look behind them as the ball races away.

children.content: Well. Well. That was one hell of a session for England going at better than five runs an over and making this bowling attack look harmless.
Mitchell Starc is looking particularly brutal on his recall, going at 7.8 an over in his seven.
The pitch isn't doing anything, so we'll see if Australia can muster something in the final session after a cuppa.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Crawley charged down at Lyon and tries to whip to leg, getting a deflection off his front pad and Carey is still able to take it cleanly down leg and take the bails off. What a star. Good bowling too to fang it down leg when he saw Crawley coming. "That's a gift. Just play sensibly," says Michael Vaughan on BBC TMS.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: CRAWLEY IS STUMPED! Masterful glovework from Alex Carey down the leg side

children.content: Crawley charged down at Lyon and tries to whip to leg, getting a deflection off his front pad and Carey is still able to take it cleanly down leg and take the bails off. What a star.

props.alt: Alex Carey celebrates stumping Zak Crawley.

children.content: Good bowling too to fang it down leg when he saw Crawley coming.
"That's a gift. Just play sensibly," says Michael Vaughan on BBC TMS.

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: England will be thrilled to see their openers make it through that awkward period, but conceding 77 runs in 90 minutes this morning is tough sledding. They'll have to start again after some scrummy scran, and so too shall we. See you back here in 40 minutes.
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: LUNCH: England 0-13 (Crawley 6, Duckett 7)

props.alt: Mitchell Starc shouts with his arms in the air as he appeals for a wicket.
